quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
1,1,"In the name of Allah, the Merciful, the Compassionate {1}",footnotes:1:One of the many practices taught by Islam is that its followers should begin their activities in the name of God. This principle
1,2,"Praise {1} be to Allah, the Lord {2} of the entire universe.",footnotes:1:In Arabic the word Rabb has three meanings: (i) Lord and Master; (ii) Sustainer
1,3,"The Merciful, the Compassionate {1}",footnotes:1:Whenever we are deeply impressed by the greatness of something we try to express our feelings by using superlatives. If the use of one superlative does not do full justice to our feelings
1,4,"The Master of the Day of Recompense {1} .",footnotes:1:God will be the Lord of the Day when all generations of mankind gather together on order to render an account of their conduct
1,5,"You alone do we worship {1} , and You alone do we turn for help {2}",footnotes:1:The term ibadah is used in three sense: (i) worship and adoration; (ii) obedience and submission; and (iii) service and subjection. In this particular context the term carries all these meanings simultaneously. In other words
1,6,"Direct us on to the Straight Way {1} ,",footnotes:1:We beseech God to guide us in all walks of life to a way which is absolutely true
1,7,"The way of those whom You have favoured {1} , who did not incur Your wrath, who are not astray {2} .",footnotes:1:This defines the 'straight way' which we ask God to open to us. It is the way which has always been followed by those who have enjoyed God's favours and blessings. This is the way which has been trodden from the beginning of time by all those individuals and communities that have unfailingly enjoyed God's favours and blessings.This makes it clear that the recipients of God's favour are not those who appear
